							{
								"paragraphOrdinal": 1,
								"paragraphTitle":  "Good job/ Bad job",
								"paragraphSubtitles": null,
								"paragraphContents": [
									"Everyone wants to have a good job, but what exactly does a ‘good job’ mean? Is it the money, the location or the hours? What about the company culture? We speak to two people with very different jobs to find out more."
								]
							},
							{
								"paragraphOrdinal": 2,
								"paragraphTitle": "Jie Chen",
								"paragraphSubtitles": null,
								"paragraphContents": [
									"I work for a small company, and the office is near my house, so I don’t have to take the subway or drive my car. I walk to work every day, and it only takes five minutes!"
								]
							},
							{
								"paragraphOrdinal": 3,
								"paragraphTitle": null,
								"paragraphSubtitles": null,
								"paragraphContents": [
									"I really like the office. It’s a nice space, and it’s very quiet and relaxing. Also, there’s an outside space, so we don’t have to stay indoors on sunny days – we can work outside!"
								]
							},
							{
								"paragraphOrdinal": 4,
								"paragraphTitle": null,
								"paragraphSubtitles": null,
								"paragraphContents": [ 
									"My salary isn’t great, but it’s okay. My favorite thing about my job is that I can choose my own hours. I don’t have to work nine to five! I usually work from seven in the morning until three in the afternoon. I’m a morning person, so I’m very happy that I can work early, and get home early, too."
								]
							},
							{
								"paragraphOrdinal": 5,
								"paragraphTitle": "Mike Carlstrom",
								"paragraphSubtitles": null,
								"paragraphContents": [ 
									"I like my job sometimes, but it isn’t easy. I’m very busy every day and I have to make a lot of important decisions."
								]
							},
							{
								"paragraphOrdinal": 6,
								"paragraphTitle": null,
								"paragraphSubtitles": null,
								"paragraphContents": [ 
									"The good thing about my job is the money – I’m very well paid. I don’t have any free time. I have to work long hours. I usually get to the office at 8:30 am, and I often leave at around 9 pm. My office is in the center of the city, and the drive from my home takes over an hour."
								]
							},	
							{
								"paragraphOrdinal": 7,
								"paragraphTitle": null,
								"paragraphSubtitles": null,
								"paragraphContents": [ 
									"Also, I often have to work on the weekend, so I don’t see my family much. I want to work from home and spend more time with my children, so my plan is to become self-employed soon."
								]
							},	
							{
								"paragraphOrdinal": 8,
								"paragraphTitle": null,
								"paragraphSubtitles": null,
								"paragraphContents": [
									"nine to five (n phrase) the hours of a typical working day in many countries",
									"salary (n) the fixed amount of money that you get for your job",
									"self-employed (adj) working for yourself, not for one company"
								]
							}	
